Taiwan Stocks: AU Optronics, Hon Hai Precision, Largan, UMC

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-03-03T01:40:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/au-optronics-asustek-hon-hai-precision-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Stocks of the following companies
had unusual price changes in Taipei trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and shares are as of 9:18 a.m. local time.  Taiwan’s Taiex Index rose 72.79, or 0.8 percent, to
8,692.69.  Apple Inc.-related shares: Foxconn Technology Co. (2354 TT),
which makes casings for Apple notebook computers, gained 2.7
percent to NT$115, the highest since Feb. 8.  Wintek Corp. (2384)  (2384
TT), a supplier of displays to Apple, advanced 1.2 percent to
NT$57.50. Largan Precision Co. (3008 TT), which makes camera
lenses for Apple, increased 1.9 percent to a record NT$841.  Apple Inc. introduced a new version of its iPad tablet
computer. The iPad 2 features a faster chip, and front and rear
cameras that allow videoconferencing. It’s also 33 percent
thinner than its predecessor, released in April.  Flat panel companies and chip companies:  AU Optronics Corp. (2409) 
(2409 TT), the island’s second-largest flat panel maker, gained
3 percent to NT$27.30, the highest since Feb. 9.  United
Microelectronics Corp. (2303)  (2303 TT), the world’s second-largest
contract maker of chips, advanced 1.3 percent to NT$15.65.  Taiwan will allow Chinese investors to take up to a 10
percent stake in local flat-panel makers and  semiconductor
companies , and less than 50 percent in ventures, the Ministry of
Economic Affairs said late yesterday in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
